Let's start with the good: The tables are not set too close to each other, giving enough privacy to each party. The environment is comfortable. Also, the server I had took really good care of us. She was always making sure we're okay. The bad: I was there for a Thanksgiving dinner, and they were charging top money. But the variety of food, as well as the quality of food, didn't deliver. I had some dark turkey meat and it was tough. I was quite disappointed. Their prime rib was too dry for the 1st piece that I ate. But thank God the second piece was much better. The food choices were not that much. I definitely think that they could add more items with the price they charged. I will likely not go back to this place in the near future.
Good service and good food price is good to especially for kamaina we will definitely return
Food was great my auntie loved the vintage tea kettle

Boring buffet, hardly worth $50.  Prime Rib is the centerpiece and it is good.  Other hot dishes are Mahi Mahi, Ox tail, chicken, rice, pasta and potatoes.  A basic salad bar, ministrone   soup, and desert round it off.  Why not add some shrimp, sushi rolls, or some asian foods?  I expected a lot more.  Glad I showed up after 8 and recieved the $25 price.  Every night is different, avoid Tuesday.

dinner buffet on tuesday is Italian inspired plus many other items and it is fantastic, prime rib done to perfection, pastas with house sauces, so many hot choices and cold items, full salad bar it's to much to list, cheese cakes, creme brulee, cupcakes, cakes, cheeses, fruit, soups..... 5 to 6pm is half price, had we found this on day 1, we would have gained 30 pounds trying all the theme nights alexis took such great care of us, try this folks, even at reg price it's worth it
Awesome Food and Awesome Service!!! Our waiter was always making sure we were good!!
Food and desserts are NOT good! My prime rib that was decent(no flavor) was cold. Waiter was awesome though the only reason it gets 3 stars. Dont waste your money.

Went on a seafood night. Generous continuous supply of crab legs, excellent poke bar and steak at the carvery. Great selection of beers, wine and cocktails on the happy hour menu. Great place to go for a bit of indulgence.

The place was clean and neat and attention to detail was taking in this decor they went out of their way to accommodate my disability and suggested possible she get around things and obstacles that was interfering. The food was there is no words to describe how good it was other than it melted in my mouth the prime of the ribs were excellent the seafood was oh well done and I have no complaints please feel free to go and visit them and they really do cater to everyone they even gave us a discount for being from Hawaii if you mention you are from why you get a discount it's called Kama' aina discount.

My wife and I met two wonderful waitress by the names Madonna and Lita. They treated us with excellent and friendly service. Madonna is a Super Star, she displayed loving affection and superior service. This encouraged us return for breakfast and dinner two weeks in a row.  Thank you both for such a great experience. Calvin & Margarett Baker
The roast beef is excellent. The setting and decoration is great. I recommend.

During our stay we frequented this restaurant because it was easy and in the hotel! We did the prime rib buffet and went during the special pricing to save some cash. The prime rib was good and the sides were...eclectic?! It isn't the standard buffet you would find on the mainland but it's got something for everyone.  Breakfast buffet is great. They change tthings out so aren't eating the same thing day after day. The POG juice is a must. A lite bit of Hawaiian sweetness to start your day (you can also request it at dinner and the lovely lady's will get you a glass of it).  Overall this was a great place for us during our stay. The lady's were always so sweet and helpful. I won't say the food is spectacular but it's good when you don't want to leave the hotel! Plus the ocean view can't be beat.
I found it to overpriced for a Buffet.

Fantastic breakfast buffet. Eggs, omlettes to order, fruit, sausage,bacon,etc. Pastry and muffins, waffles and pancakes. But the best thing about the buffet is the waitress Janice. She is a treasure, and totally pampered my wife and me. 5 Star buffet, but 10 Star service! My wife actually fell off her chair while getting up. Janice's kindness and attention was incredible. Also Tony and Anna from security, and the manager Donna were incredible. Thank you Marriott for a staff that is beyond compare.

It's a hidden temple, full of delicious dishes, like going to a medieval feast at the King & Queen castle. One of the best place for fresh island "poke", I recommend visiting the carving table, at least five times,  the chef was generous on the size and cut of the "prime rib", which I also considered scrumptious,  melts-in-mouth, just like "butter!" moment 😋. Don't  forget the crab legs and the hot entrees,  and desserts 🤤 Service by waiter was excellent,  kept taking away empty plates and refilled drinks right in time.  This place even have a private room for parties! So, let's keep Kuhio Restaurant & Grill a secret, we surely don't want everyone finding out about this place🤐. Then we're never be able to be easily seated, we'd have to stand in a long line and wait days to experience their 5 Star🌟 "poke" bar. But again, it's worth it.  Life is too short! Aloha👋

Great food and fresh snow crabs. The prime rib was perfect! The food always looks fresh. The seating and atmosphere is comfortable. Definitely a monthly treat now. The Kamaaina rate is 20% off.
The prime rib buffet is fantastic, with additional entrees changing every night.  And half off Sunday through Thursday...can't beat it.  Great low carb option.

very average quality food for the dinner buffet.  the prime rib is oviously the best thing on the menu, but is just ok, not exceptional.  the only way this place is remotely worth it is for the weekday half price offer, which brings the cost down to $23 from $46.  however, they do not publish this, nor warn you in any way, but they force a15% of original price tip with the offer.  anotherwords, the $23 buffet has almost a $7  mandatory tip added, which you aren't told about until you get the bill.  the service is average at best, not particularly good. i would have probably tipped just 10% of original or 15% of the reduced price, since it was a buffet, and the waitress wasn't there much.  i even had to go to the bar to get thigs like e tra napkins, and find someone to request more water...   not worth a $7/pp forced, uundisclosed, tip for the brief meal  in my opinion...

As of October 2018, Prime rib dinner buffet on a Tuesday was $46 per person.  There is an early bird discount of 50%, but the 15% tip is added automatically.  The place sort of does Theme nights.  Tuesday is Italian night, which translates to having 2 pasta dishes, chicken piccata, oxtail Milanese, and Minnestrone soup.  The Italian dishes were ok, the only standout being the Oxtail Milanese served with polenta.  The Prime rib was very tender.  Good quality beef, and much better than normal buffet roast beef.  The buffet also has your regular salad and vegetable sides, along with a nice looking dessert table.  It was an ok dinner for a rainy day unless you are a big meat eater.  It works well when you don’t have to leave the hotel.

I had breakfast buffet covered though a conference.  The choices of food was pretty plentiful from fresh fruit to the usual eggs and bacon. There was someone always at the grill cooking up any requests I believe. They offered 3 types of juice and I always go the POG juice.  It can get busy and initially I felt that they were kinda "cold". I then realized that it is because they are busy.  I understood and I made effort to be a good customer to them with thanks and appreciation.  I felt immediately after that, I felt a shift in communication, even though they were busy.  Kim (who is in the morning) was super nice.  The amount of food was great. The normal cost is $32. The staff do try to keep the place clean by cleaning right after a customer is done.  The dinner menu was pretty good too.

Excellent service, fare, and dining area.

Celebrated my husband’s (63rd) and our eldest granddaughter’s(26th) birthdays and the food served at their buffet is absolutely tasty and abundantly filled with assorted entrees and desserts.  Prime rib and crab legs were a sure hit with our family too!  The staff went above and beyond in their service expertise. Their ambience makes one feel you’ve just stepped into beautiful fine dining. Kamaainas receive 20% off, and being a special occasion it was well worth the price.  I definitely recommend Kuhio Beach Grill  to both our visitors and locals here in the islands.
Great breakfast Madonna is the best server very friendly and outgoing highly recommend
Great food good chefs good buffets watch out for prime rib night and all you can eat crab 2/3 times a week good value too.

As an elite member for Marriott they offered me a 25% discount to try one of the restaurants in the hotel. Usually this is because the food costs much more simply because of convenience. So I decided to walk downstairs to the Kuhio Beach Grill. When I entered I was seated towards the back of the room. Was there something wrong with flip flops, shorts and a t-shirt? This is Waikiki Beach after all... So after some consideration and seeing the full menu I opted for the Wednesday Asian Buffet. I would guess there were over 30 quality items, excluding desserts. I did my best to sample much. I had a salad, a slice of prime rib (very good), Lemon chicken, teriyaki tidbits, steamed rice, fish & a shrimp. then I ordered and drank my first mai tai and had desserts. The regular buffet price is $24.95 monday thru friday. Considering this is an "All you can eat" it is very valued. The food is very well prepared, heated and the staff are the friendliest I have met during my week stay. Give it a try, you won't regret it.

This place has gone downhill. The prime rib is smaller and the crab legs went smaller too. They now serve this snow crab legs instead that are so skinny. It's not even worth your time picking it of the meat. The chef gives you a small slice of prime rib and if you go back he'll give you even a smaller slice. The selection of other foods was small.
